{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.6",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 6 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:1",
      "text": "My son, if you have become surety for your neighbor, have given your pledge for a stranger;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:2",
      "text": "if you are snared in the utterance of your lips, caught in the words of your mouth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:3",
      "text": "then do this, my son, and save yourself, for you have come into your neighbor's power: go, hasten, and importune your neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:4",
      "text": "Give your eyes no sleep and your eyelids no slumber;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:5",
      "text": "save yourself like a gazelle from the hunter, like a bird from the hand of the fowler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:6",
      "text": "Go to the ant, O sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:7",
      "text": "Without having any chief, officer or ruler,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:8",
      "text": "she prepares her food in summer, and gathers her sustenance in harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:9",
      "text": "How long will you lie there, O sluggard? When will you arise from your sleep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:10",
      "text": "A little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:11",
      "text": "and poverty will come upon you like a vagabond, and want like an armed man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:12",
      "text": "A worthless person, a wicked man, goes about with crooked speech,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:13",
      "text": "winks with his eyes, scrapes with his feet, points with his finger,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:14",
      "text": "with perverted heart devises evil, continually sowing discord;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:15",
      "text": "therefore calamity will come upon him suddenly; in a moment he will be broken beyond healing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:16",
      "text": "There are six things which the Lord hates, seven which are an abomination to him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:17",
      "text": "haughty eyes, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:18",
      "text": "a heart that devises wicked plans, feet that make haste to run to evil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:19",
      "text": "a false witness who breathes out lies, and a man who sows discord among brothers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:20",
      "text": "My son, keep your father's commandment, and forsake not your mother's teaching.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:21",
      "text": "Bind them upon your heart always; tie them about your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:22",
      "text": "When you walk, they will lead you; when you lie down, they will watch over you; and when you awake, they will talk with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:23",
      "text": "For the commandment is a lamp and the teaching a light, and the reproofs of discipline are the way of life,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:24",
      "text": "to preserve you from the evil woman, from the smooth tongue of the adventuress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:25",
      "text": "Do not desire her beauty in your heart, and do not let her capture you with her eyelashes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:26",
      "text": "for a harlot may be hired for a loaf of bread, but an adulteress stalks a man's very life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:27",
      "text": "Can a man carry fire in his bosom and his clothes not be burned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:28",
      "text": "Or can one walk upon hot coals and his feet not be scorched?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:29",
      "text": "So is he who goes in to his neighbor's wife; none who touches her will go unpunished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:30",
      "text": "Do not men despise a thief if he steals to satisfy his appetite when he is hungry?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:31",
      "text": "And if he is caught, he will pay sevenfold; he will give all the goods of his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:32",
      "text": "He who commits adultery has no sense; he who does it destroys himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:33",
      "text": "Wounds and dishonor will he get, and his disgrace will not be wiped away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:34",
      "text": "For jealousy makes a man furious, and he will not spare when he takes revenge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.6.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:35",
      "text": "He will accept no compensation, nor be appeased though you multiply gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
